commitResults.messageBody:
This ensures better testing: test TagManager is now functionally identical to regular (production) TagManager.

* Remove unowned reference in Tag to TagManager: this fixes problems with encoding (classes don't play well with Codable)

* Update Tag.value implementation to use optional cached TagManager: fixes infinite loop

Computed properties aren't as lazy as thought. The original implementation uses TagManager.create().getDisplayValue(). When creating a TagManager through TagManager.create(), Tags are instantiated, which calls TagManager.create(), which instantiates Tags... 

To fix this, instead of calling TagManager.create(), we directly reference the cached TagManager object. However, it may not have been instantiated yet (unavailable). We return an empty string during unavailability, which should never happen in normal usage.
